article.headline: Kennesaw St. 59, Gardner-Webb 56
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Ronell Wooten scored 20 of his 22 points in the first half and Golden Ingle scored his 10 in the second half, including a pair of free throws with nine seconds remaining, to give Kennesaw State a 59-56 victory over Gardner-Webb on Sunday. The Owls (10-15, 6-7 Atlantic Sun) twice saw their lead reduced to one point in the final 92 seconds -- first on a pair of free throws by Matt French with 1:32 to go and then on a French layup with 47 seconds remaining. Gardner-Webb (7-17, 6-7) was led by Takayo Siddle's 15 points. French added 10. Wooten, who made 7 of 13 shots, had five 3-point baskets in the first half.
